What you need to know:  Cherono clocked a season’s best of 8:40.29 for her first Diamond League victory since 2015, beating Briton Amy-Eloise Markovc to second place in PB 8:40.32.But Cherono had to give a frantic chase before overtaking Markovc in the last 30m to win.“I'm so delighted to win today. I had to push myself harder in the last 15m after I took charge  and that resulted in achieving my season best. I now need to get ready for the trials for the World championship,” said Cherono.